  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Elderly patients show different pharmacokinetic and pharmacodynamic variables and usually
      need smaller doses of anesthetic drugs than younger patients. The purpose of this study was
      to investigate the optimal effect-site concentration of remifentanil for preventing injection
      pain during propofol induction in elderly patients by the Dixon's up-and-down method.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
